{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, CNNs typically focus on global features and may overlook long-distance dependencies and critical local features within the image, which are essential for accurately classifying remote sensing scenes that contain diverse objects.",
    "To overcome these limitations, we combine a lightweight residual structure with a channel attention mechanism, specifically the squeeze-and-excitation (SE) network, into the proposed RCA network.The motivation behind combining the channel attention mechanism with CNNs is to leverage the strengths of each approach: CNNs excel at extracting hierarchical spatial features, while channel attention mechanisms, such as the SE network, enhance the model's ability to focus on the most relevant feature channels, which traditional CNNs tend to ignore.",
    "The residual connections in the RCA network ensure effective multi-scale feature extraction, allowing the network to handle both fine and coarse details without the degradation of learning performance.",
    "This helps mitigate issues such as vanishing gradients, which are common in deep networks, enabling the network to learn more complex relationships between input and output data.",
    "The SE network plays a pivotal role by adaptively recalibrating the feature responses across channels."
  ]
}